and the moist star Upon whose influence Neptune s empire stands Was sick almost to doomsday with eclipse And even the like precurse of fierce As harbingers preceding still the fates And prologue to the omen coming Have heaven and earth together demonstrated Unto our climature and countrymen Enter Ghost again But soft ! behold where it comes again ! I ll cross though it blast me Stay illusion ! Spreads his arms If thou hast any or use of Speak to me If there be any good thing to be That may to thee do race to Speak to me If thou art privy to thy country s Which happily foreknowing may speak ! Or if thou hast uphoarded in thy life Extorted treasure in the womb of earth (For which, they say, you spirits oft walk in death)
